           SPELL=gnash
         VERSION=20051226
          SOURCE=$SPELL-$VERSION.tar.bz2
SOURCE_DIRECTORY=$BUILD_DIRECTORY/$SPELL-0.7
   SOURCE_URL[0]=http://www.gnu.org/software/gnash/releases/$SOURCE
#   SOURCE_URL[0]=$GNU_URL/$SPELL/releases/$SOURCE
      SOURCE_GPG="gurus.gpg:${SOURCE}.sig"
        WEB_SITE=http://www.gnu.org/software/gnash/
         ENTERED=20060113
         UPDATED=20060113
       BUILD_API=2
           SHORT='GNU Flash movie player'
cat << EOF
Gnash is a GNU Flash movie player. Till now it has been possible to play flash
movies with proprietary software. While there are a few free flash players,
none supports anything higher than SWF v4 at best.  Gnash is based on GameSWF,
and supports many SWF v7 features.

Features:
* Runs standalone
  Gnash can run standalone to play flash movies
* Firefox plugin
  Gnash can also run as a plugin from within Firefox.
* SWF v7 compliant
  Gnash can play many current flash movies.
* XML Message server
  Gnash also supports an XML based message system as is documented in the Flash
  Format specification.
* High Quality Output
  Gnash uses OpenGL for rendering the graphics.
* Free Software
  Gnash is 100% free software. For more information on the GPL, go to the Free
  Software Foundation web site.
EOF
